# CH341A Flash Attempt Log — 2026-04-02
# Equipment: CH341A (1a86:5512) + 1.8V adapter + SOP8 clip
# Target: Winbond W25Q16JWN (25Q16JWN, date 2105, blue dot pin 1)
# Software: flashrom v1.7.0, NixOS Linux 6.18.18
# Flash computer: Ryzen 9 desktop, front USB-A port

## USB Detection (CH341A standalone, no clip)
$ sudo dmesg | tail -20
[286020.357464] usb 1-2.3.4: new full-speed USB device number 13 using xhci_hcd
[286020.445950] usb 1-2.3.4: New USB device found, idVendor=1a86, idProduct=5512, bcdDevice= 3.04
[286020.445955] usb 1-2.3.4: New USB device strings: Mfr=0, Product=2, SerialNumber=0
[286020.445957] usb 1-2.3.4: Product: USB UART-LPT

## Baseline Test (no clip attached)
$ sudo flashrom -p ch341a_spi
flashrom v1.7.0 on Linux 6.18.18 (x86_64)
flashrom is free software, get the source code at https://flashrom.org
No EEPROM/flash device found.
# EXPECTED — confirms programmer works

## Attempt 1: Clip on chip with 1.8V adapter (rear USB)
$ sudo flashrom -p ch341a_spi
cb_out: error: LIBUSB_TRANSFER_TIMED_OUT
config_stream: Failed to write 3 bytes
Could not configure stream interface.
Error: Programmer initialization failed.
# CH341A LED: green → red
# Side effect: rear xHCI controller crashed

## dmesg after crash
[307101.534249] xhci_hcd 0000:07:00.1: HC died; cleaning up
[307101.534293] spi-ch341 1-2.3.4:1.0: probe with driver spi-ch341 failed with error -110

## Attempt 2: Reseated clip, front USB port
$ sudo flashrom -p ch341a_spi
No EEPROM/flash device found.
# Clip not making contact

## Attempt 3: Forced chip detection
$ sudo flashrom -p ch341a_spi -c W25Q16.W
No EEPROM/flash device found.
# Still no contact

## Attempt 4: Reseated clip firmly
$ sudo flashrom -p ch341a_spi
cb_in: error: LIBUSB_TRANSFER_TIMED_OUT
ch341a_spi_spi_send_command: Failed to read 4 bytes
cb_out: error: LIBUSB_TRANSFER_TIMED_OUT
ch341a_spi_spi_send_command: Failed to write 37 bytes
[... ~30 more timeout errors, transitioning to LIBUSB_TRANSFER_STALL ...]
# Programmer IS trying to talk SPI but every transaction fails
# CH341A LED: red

## Attempt 5: Without 1.8V adapter (diagnostic)
# Clipped SOP8 directly CH341A → chip (no adapter)
# CH341A LED: stayed GREEN — no crash
# Confirms: 1.8V adapter is the failure point

## USB controller degradation timeline
1. Rear xHCI crashed (HC died) — rear ports dead
2. CH341A repeatedly crashed on front USB, recovered after replug
3. Front USB started dropping devices (webcam)
4. Session ended — desktop reboot required to reset USB controllers
